&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Partnerize, we&#39;re on a mission to transform the way businesses grow. We&#39;ve built the leading partnership automation platform that empowers brands to discover, engage, and convert their audiences at scale. From affiliate marketing to influencer collaborations, we help our clients build and manage profitable partnerships that drive real results. We&#39;re a team of passionate problem-solvers who are dedicated to helping our clients win in the ever-evolving world of digital marketing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for passionate, talented people who want to be part of a winning team. At Partnerize, you&#39;ll find a culture of collaboration, innovation, and respect. We&#39;re guided by our core values, and we&#39;re committed to creating an environment where everyone can do their best work. We also offer a competitive salary, generous benefits, and a flexible work environment that allows you to thrive both personally and professionally. If you&#39;re ready to grow your career and make a difference, we&#39;d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Account Strategist is distinguished by a dedicated focus on client satisfaction within the affiliate marketing ecosystem, realized through strong verbal and written communication skills. The Account Strategist will be responsible for providing superior affiliate strategic support for our Brand partners, managing a portfolio of client relationships, and driving revenue growth through strategic publisher optimization. They should excel at relationship building, analyzing affiliate marketing campaigns (including tracking, conversion data, and ROI metrics), and identifying performance trends. The successful candidate will be an aggressive self-starter with a deep understanding of the affiliate industry and must possess an unbelievably strong work ethic, intelligence, sense of urgency, positive attitude, tenacity, and a desire to put the customer first every day. The employee must have the ability to execute and scale affiliate strategies and special assignments under only general supervision. The employee must have a personal sense of integrity, commitment, and professionalism. This position provides high growth potential for candidates looking to build a career in a rapidly expanding affiliate marketing industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*This is a hybrid role and will require 2 days/week in our London office. This is mandatory and candidates that are not able to work in the office as required will not be considered for this position.*&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead a portfolio of established and emerging brands on objectives and KPIs for success with their affiliate strategy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct on affiliate program strategy, actionable tactics and their execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct robust reporting and deliver analytical insights to guide strategic recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead weekly client calls; and proactively communicate reporting, new opportunities, and progress against objectives&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and conduct online and in-person client presentations with excellence&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Forecast budgets for customers and Partnerize&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in renewals and contract negotiations&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with team members in developing and sourcing affiliate opportunities&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;What you will achieve: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
